By December 31, 1991, the Department, after consulting with local government and the real estate development, building, and environmental communities, shall adopt regulations, including the development of guidance manuals to:
Implement this subtitle and set requirements and standards which establish:
Standards of performance required in forest stand delineations and forest conservation plans including the submittal process;
Criteria for local forest conservation programs; and
Implementation processes for the Department's administration in the absence of a local forest conservation program;
Assist and guide local authorities in the development of their local forest conservation program by providing:
Training of local officials; and
A model local government ordinance that meets the requirements of this subtitle; and
Assist developers, planners, surveyors, engineers, foresters, biologists, and landscape architects in:
Developing methodology and gathering natural resource information required in the preparation of a forest stand delineation and a forest conservation plan;
Determining the size, location, and orientation of forest areas to be retained;
Determining the size, location, and orientation of areas to be afforested or reforested;
Implementing protection techniques and devices used in preserving specimen trees or areas designated for retention during construction; and
Determining species, spacing, and timing of afforestation or reforestation.
